'''''Strategy X''''' (ス卜ラテジーX) is a vertically [[Shoot 'em up|scrolling shooter]] released as an [[arcade video game]] by [[Konami]] in 1981. It was licensed to [[Stern (game company)|Stern Electronics]] for US distribution. The player controls a tank through various stages, defeating enemies and picking up fuel. Konami published an [[Atari 2600]] version in 1983.<ref name="mania">{{cite web |title=Strategy X |url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-2600-vcs-strategy-x_11809.html |website=Atari Mania}}</ref>

==Reception==
In a retrospective look, [[AllGame]] said, "''Strategy X''{{'}}s graphics are colorful, but not always helpful in terms of figuring out what's going on".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Green |first1=Earl |title=Strategy X - Review |url=http://www.allgame.com/game.php?id=11184&tab=review |website=[[AllGame]] |access-date=26 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141115020730/http://www.allgame.com/game.php?id=11184&tab=review |archive-date=15 November 2014 |url-status=dead}}</ref>

